<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,931,1102]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[365,512,931,957]" name="South Africa" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, this species has a much shorter preocular projection (
<figureCitation box="[1136,1203,931,958]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[192,1385,390,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[192,1396,382,1832]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Ophthalmothrips species. Head, 1–4: (1) amyae females; (2) breviceps male; (3) conocephalus female from Madagascar; (4) faurei female from Japan. (5) amyae female tergite III. Male fore tibia and tarsus 6–8: (6) amyae; (7) conocephalus; (8) faurei. (9) amyae female pelta; (10) conocephalus male pelta and tergite II; (11) faurei male pelta; (12) conocephalus male interocellar setae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3258655/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) than its congeners. Pelta broadly hat-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[443,511,967,994]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[192,1385,390,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[192,1396,382,1832]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Ophthalmothrips species. Head, 1–4: (1) amyae females; (2) breviceps male; (3) conocephalus female from Madagascar; (4) faurei female from Japan. (5) amyae female tergite III. Male fore tibia and tarsus 6–8: (6) amyae; (7) conocephalus; (8) faurei. (9) amyae female pelta; (10) conocephalus male pelta and tergite II; (11) faurei male pelta; (12) conocephalus male interocellar setae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3258655/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), wing-retaining setae small and not sigmoid (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1099,967,994]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[192,1385,390,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[192,1396,382,1832]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Ophthalmothrips species. Head, 1–4: (1) amyae females; (2) breviceps male; (3) conocephalus female from Madagascar; (4) faurei female from Japan. (5) amyae female tergite III. Male fore tibia and tarsus 6–8: (6) amyae; (7) conocephalus; (8) faurei. (9) amyae female pelta; (10) conocephalus male pelta and tergite II; (11) faurei male pelta; (12) conocephalus male interocellar setae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3258655/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Female with tergite IX setae S1 slightly longer than tube, sharply pointed at apex. Male brachypterous, female brachypterous or macropterous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
